              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Carbon target foil served as a secondary",
                "emission foil for target microchannel plate detector",
                "for time of flight detector."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Evaporation residues (ER - mainly 30Si, 29Si,",
                "28Si, 29Al, 28Al, 27Mg, and 26Mg) were detected by",
                "two annular Si detectors, which subtended angular",
                "range 3.5 deg - 25 deg. ER were identified by time of",
                "flight end energy loss in Si detectors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Energy was determined by time of flight"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A beam of 18-O ions, accelerated to an energy of 80.7",
                "MeV, impinged on a deuterium gas cell at a pressure",
                "of 350 torr and cooled to a temperature of 77 K. Ions",
                "of 19-O were produced via a (d,p) reaction. Reaction",
                "products were partly separated from the incident beam",
                "by the electromagnetic spectrometer RESOLUT. Although",
                "this spectrometer rejected most of the unreacted",
                "beam that exited the production gas cell, the beam",
                "exiting the spectrometer consisted of both 19-O and",
                "18-O ions necessitating identification of each ion on",
                "a particle-by-particle basis. ions were identified by",
                "time of flight and energy loss. 19-O ions",
                "corresponded to approximately 31% of the beam",
                "intensity, 18-O-7+ and 18-O-6+ represented to",
                "approximately 20% and 29%, respectively. 19-O beam",
                "incident on the target was (1.5 - 4)E+3 ions/s."
              ]
            }
          ],
